ASSET PURCHASE AGREEMENT

This Asset Purchase Agreement ("Agreement") is made this 20th day of January, 2025, between HORIZON CAPITAL PARTNERS, LP, a Delaware limited partnership ("Buyer"), and MERIDIAN TECHNOLOGIES, INC., a Delaware corporation ("Seller").

RECITALS

WHEREAS, Seller owns and operates a business engaged in the development and manufacture of advanced semiconductor components for automotive applications;

WHEREAS, Buyer desires to acquire substantially all of the assets of Seller's business; and

WHEREAS, the parties desire to set forth the terms and conditions of such acquisition.

NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual covenants contained herein, the parties agree as follows:

1. PURCHASE AND SALE OF ASSETS

1.1 Assets to be Purchased. Subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement, Seller agrees to sell, transfer, and deliver to Buyer, and Buyer agrees to purchase from Seller, all of Seller's right, title, and interest in and to the following assets (collectively, the "Purchased Assets"):

(a) All tangible personal property, including machinery, equipment, furniture, fixtures, supplies, and inventory;
(b) All intellectual property, including patents, trademarks, copyrights, trade secrets, and know-how;
(c) All contracts and agreements listed in Schedule 1.1(c);
(d) All customer lists, supplier lists, and business records;
(e) All goodwill associated with the business.

1.2 Excluded Assets. The following assets shall be excluded from the sale (the "Excluded Assets"):
(a) Cash and cash equivalents
(b) Accounts receivable arising prior to Closing
(c) Real estate owned by Seller
(d) Employee benefit plans and related assets

2. PURCHASE PRICE

2.1 Purchase Price. The total purchase price for the Purchased Assets shall be Eighty-Five Million Dollars ($85,000,000) (the "Purchase Price").

2.2 Payment Terms. The Purchase Price shall be paid as follows:
(a) $17,000,000 in cash at Closing
(b) $68,000,000 through delivery of promissory note bearing 4.5% annual interest

3. REPRESENTATIONS AND WARRANTIES

3.1 Seller's Representations. Seller represents and warrants that:
(a) It has full corporate power and authority to execute this Agreement
(b) The execution and performance of this Agreement have been duly authorized
(c) No material adverse change has occurred in Seller's business since December 31, 2024
(d) All intellectual property is owned free and clear of liens and encumbrances
(e) There are no pending or threatened legal proceedings against Seller

3.2 Buyer's Representations. Buyer represents and warrants that:
(a) It has full power and authority to execute this Agreement
(b) It has sufficient funds to complete the transaction
(c) It has conducted satisfactory due diligence

4. COVENANTS

4.1 Non-Competition. For a period of five (5) years following Closing, Seller shall not directly or indirectly compete with the business being sold within the United States.

4.2 Employee Matters. Buyer shall offer employment to all current employees of Seller on substantially similar terms for a period of at least one year.

5. CONDITIONS TO CLOSING

5.1 Conditions to Buyer's Obligations:
(a) Hart-Scott-Rodino antitrust clearance
(b) No material adverse change in Seller's business
(c) Delivery of all required closing documents

5.2 Conditions to Seller's Obligations:
(a) Delivery of Purchase Price
(b) No material adverse change in Buyer's financial condition

6. INDEMNIFICATION

6.1 Seller shall indemnify Buyer for:
(a) Breaches of representations and warranties
(b) Excluded liabilities
(c) Pre-closing tax liabilities

6.2 Indemnification shall be limited to $8.5 million and claims must be brought within 18 months of Closing.

7. MISCELLANEOUS

7.1 Governing Law. This Agreement shall be governed by Delaware law.

7.2 Entire Agreement. This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement between the parties.

IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties have executed this Agreement as of the date first written above.

